hopobject.body: Very interesting tale hemangiomatreatment.org Ever since the opening up of Japan in the mid-19th century, its gardens have fascinated Western visitors. Assemblages of rocks, gravel and a few dwarf trees have always seemed the antithesis of our gardens, so full of flowers, colour and a desire to show off. Many garden designers have described how they have sought inspiration in the ascetic dignity, purity and discipline of the traditional Japanese garden.
